      "message": "this one is complex enough, that I'm not sure that carrying the whole signature buys much.  In addition, as this loop is short and only two methods are used within the it, I don't think we're losing much their either.  Always a trade-off in maintainability: better to use long things (e.g., type declarations and variable names) that make it more obvious what is happening, or better to keep things short so it's easier to take it all in with a glance.\n\nI'm OK either way, but this is one of the few cases I've seen where it might make sense to use \"var\".",
